{"title":"Tom's Wife","plot":"Using a then proto-type lens that would later revolutionize digital video's ability to have a true filmic quality, Tom's Wife was a monumental achievement in micro-budget cinema. An authentically period drama shot on practical sets in Elgin, Texas, using meticulously selected antique props and costumes, carefully researched colloquial dialogue, and a cast of talented unknowns, Tom's Wife was called \"a sincere and austere feature that vividly convey period flavor,\" by Variety Magazine. The filmmakers diligently crafted a quiet and honest Depression era story of a young woman trapped in an abusive marriage who finds grace in the friendship of her neighbor, and hope in the love of a traveling salesman. Garnering awards at festivals all over the world, Tom's Wife offers a glimpse into the scope of truly independent cinema and will be a joy to watch for anyone looking for a story with heart and dignity.","genres":["Drama"],"stems":["Using","a","then","proto-typ","len","that","would","later","revolution","digit","video","'s","abil","to","have","a","true","filmic","qualiti",",","Tom","'s","Wife","was","a","monument","achiev","in","micro-budget","cinema",".","An","authent","period","drama","shot","on","practic","set","in","Elgin",",","Texa",",","use","meticul","select","antiqu","prop","and","costum",",","care","research","colloqui","dialogu",",","and","a","cast","of","talent","unknown",",","Tom","'s","Wife","was","call","\"","a","sincer","and","auster","featur","that","vivid","convey","period","flavor",",","\"","by","Varieti","Magazin",".","The","filmmak","dilig","craft","a","quiet","and","honest","Depress","era","stori","of","a","young","woman","trap","in","an","abus","marriag","who","find","grace","in","the","friendship","of","her","neighbor",",","and","hope","in","the","love","of","a","travel","salesman",".","Garner","award","at","festiv","all","over","the","world",",","Tom","'s","Wife","offer","a","glimps","into","the","scope","of","truli